{
  "answer": "The ghazal is found in *Diwan-E-Zauq* by Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, chapter 53 (\"baadam do jo bheje hain batwe mein daal kar\").[^1]\n\n**Matla (opening couplet):**  \n> These almonds that you sent, a gift however small,  \n> My faith demands I give my eyes and answer to the call.[^2]\n\n**Potter's-wheel couplet:**  \n> No perfect vessel from the wheel will form at all,  \n> So do not waste this heart-dust on the potter's call.[^3]\n\n[^1]: /works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/53-baadam-do-jo-bheje-hain-batwe-mein-daal-kar/translation/\n[^2]: /works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/53-baadam-do-jo-bheje-hain-batwe-mein-daal-kar/translation/#p-d86b48\n[^3]: /works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/53-baadam-do-jo-bheje-hain-batwe-mein-daal-kar/translation/#p-290709",
